Excellent release. Thanks SecretMyth and seeders.

@zax: "kimahri 480p means there are 480 progressive lines."

Very basically, 480p refers to "DVD" resolution, 720p to "HD" resolution, and 1080p to "full HD" or "Blu-ray" resolution. Each has about twice as many pixels as the previous. More pixels means higher definition (duh!), clarity and detail.
